quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  54,23,"[The people of] Thamud denied the warnings"
  54,24,"and they said, ‘Are we to follow a lone human from ourselves?! Indeed then we would be in error and madness.’"
  54,25,"‘Has the Reminder been cast upon him from among us? No, he is a self-conceited liar.’"
  54,26,‘Tomorrow they will know who is a self-conceited liar
  54,27,We are sending the She-camel as a trial for them; so watch them and be steadfast
  54,28,Inform them that the water is to be shared between them; each of them showing up at his turn.’
  54,29,"But they called their companion, and he took [a knife] and hamstrung [her]"
  54,30,So how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,31,"We sent against them a single Cry, and they became like the dry sticks of a corral builder"
  54,32,Certainly We have made the Quran simple for the sake of admonishment. So is there anyone who will be admonished
  54,33,And the people of Lot denied the warnings
  54,34,"We unleashed upon them a rain of stones, excepting the family of Lot, whom We delivered at dawn"
  54,35,as a blessing from Us. Thus do We reward those who give thanks
  54,36,"He had already warned them of Our punishment, but they disputed the warnings"
  54,37,"They even solicited of him his guests, whereat We blotted out their eyes, [saying,] ‘Taste My punishment and My warnings!’"
  54,38,Early at dawn there visited them an abiding punishment
  54,39,‘Taste My punishment and warnings!’
  54,40,Certainly We have made the Quran simple for the sake of admonishment. So is there anyone who will be admonished